<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-49-0167 </DOCNO><TEXT>In the summer of 1987 the study 'Renewable energy. A plan for the future'was published. The meaning of this plan for the present politics is discussed.A representant of the Centre for Energy Conservation and Clear Technologyanswers the question which policy relevant starting-points such a frameworkfor speculation has for stimulating renewable energy in the short term.Some recommendations are given with regard to the use of solar energy.2 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>